            <div type="translation">
                <p>
                    <lb n="1"/>Not usefully translated. 
                    <lb n="2"/>Line 1: [--?--] from the right
                    <lb n="3"/>Lines 1-4: [--?--] with the glory of the Lord and from [--?--]
                    <lb n="4"/>Line 5: [--?--] shadow of
                    <lb n="5"/>Line 6: [--?--]
                    <lb n="6"/>Lines 7-10: At the judgment, do not condemn [me] to their midst (<ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>, 75).
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Some words are partially preserved and therefore we are unaware of their origin and meaning. The text ends with a cross with four rays in the angles. Οnly the phrases: ἐν τῷ μέσῳ τῶν ἐν τῆ κρίσει μὴ κρίνῃς, in lines 7-10 are understandable. Text: Unknown.</p>
